(1, 1, 'Introduction to WordPress Development', 'introduction-to-wordpress-development', NULL, '{\"topics\":[\"1\",\"2\"],\"course_id\":\"1\"}', '<p>This lesson provides an overview of WordPress development, focusing on creating plugins and themes. It covers the basics of WordPress architecture, file structure, and the role of plugins and themes in extending WordPress functionality.</p>', '<p>This lesson provides an overview of WordPress development, focusing on creating plugins and themes. It covers the basics of WordPress architecture, file structure, and the role of plugins and themes in extending WordPress functionality.</p>\r\n<p>Firstly, we want to express our excitement about having you as a part of this course. We believe that learning is a lifelong process, and we commend your commitment to expanding your knowledge and skills. Over the duration of this course, we aim to create an engaging and interactive learning environment where you can actively participate and grow.</p>\r\n<p><iframe class=\"bd-class-lesson-video\" title=\"Sycho Psd to HTML | Class #1 : Salim Rana | 2021\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WY44eFBjZQs?list=PLLEaOX05IZa5q00MT47e3ELbmve-3KM5h\"></iframe></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', '2023-03-07 03:54:53', '2023-06-13 08:31:46'),
(2, 1, 'WordPress Plugin Development', 'wordpress-plugin-development', NULL, '{\"topics\":[\"3\",\"4\",\"5\"],\"course_id\":\"1\"}', '<p>In this lesson, learners will dive into the world of WordPress plugin development. They will learn how to create custom functionality by developing plugins, including hooks, filters, and utilizing the WordPress API to interact with core features.</p>', '<p>In this lesson, learners will dive into the world of WordPress plugin development. They will learn how to create custom functionality by developing plugins, including hooks, filters, and utilizing the WordPress API to interact with core features.</p>\r\n<p>At its core, the Python Application Engine provides a platform for hosting and running Python-based web applications. It abstracts away much of the infrastructure management, allowing developers to focus on writing code and building functionality. The engine handles the deployment, scaling, and monitoring aspects, providing a seamless experience for developers.</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"Sycho Psd to HTML Hero Area | Class #2 : Salim Rana | 2021\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Y7TFx4Y4mnM?list=PLLEaOX05IZa5q00MT47e3ELbmve-3KM5h\"></iframe></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', '2023-03-07 03:54:53', '2023-06-13 08:35:19'),
(3, 1, 'WordPress Theme Development', 'wordpress-theme-development', NULL, '{\"topics\":[null],\"course_id\":\"1\"}', '<p>This lesson focuses on WordPress theme development, teaching learners how to design and develop custom themes. Topics include template hierarchy, creating custom templates, implementing responsive design, and integrating CSS and JavaScript.</p>', '<p>This lesson focuses on WordPress theme development, teaching learners how to design and develop custom themes. Topics include template hierarchy, creating custom templates, implementing responsive design, and integrating CSS and JavaScript..</p>\r\n<p>Algorithm comparison involves analyzing and assessing different algorithms based on various factors such as time complexity, space complexity, and performance. Time complexity refers to the amount of time an algorithm takes to run, while space complexity refers to the amount of memory or storage it requires. These factors are essential considerations as they impact the efficiency and effectiveness of an algorithm.</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"Sycho Psd to HTML Features Section | Class #3 : Salim Rana | 2021\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/uchaXsjMLqw?list=PLLEaOX05IZa5q00MT47e3ELbmve-3KM5h\"></iframe></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', '2023-03-07 03:54:53', '2023-06-13 08:36:54'),
(4, 1, 'Plugin Development Best Practices', 'plugin-development-best-practices', NULL, '{\"topics\":[\"6\",\"7\"],\"course_id\":\"1\"}', '<p>This lesson emphasizes best practices for WordPress plugin development. Learners will explore techniques for writing secure and efficient code, following WordPress coding standards, handling data securely, and optimizing plugin performance.</p>', '<p>This lesson emphasizes best practices for WordPress plugin development. Learners will explore techniques for writing secure and efficient code, following WordPress coding standards, handling data securely, and optimizing plugin performance.</p>\r\n<p>Data manipulation tools provide a set of operations and functions that enable users to perform tasks such as filtering, sorting, aggregating, joining, and transforming data. These tools offer a user-friendly interface or programming environment, allowing users to interact with the data and apply desired operations with ease.</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"Sycho Psd to HTML Services Section | Class #5 : Salim Rana | 2021\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-ihgOmLvb8c?list=PLLEaOX05IZa5q00MT47e3ELbmve-3KM5h\"></iframe></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', '2023-03-07 03:54:53', '2023-06-13 08:38:35'),
(5, 1, 'Theme Development Best Practices', 'theme-development-best-practices', NULL, '{\"topics\":[\"8\",\"9\",\"10\",\"11\",\"12\",\"13\"],\"course_id\":\"1\"}', '<p>This lesson covers best practices for WordPress theme development. Learners will discover techniques to create fast, SEO-friendly themes, including optimizing images, implementing caching, utilizing responsive design, and adhering to SEO principles.</p>', '<p>This lesson covers best practices for WordPress theme development. Learners will discover techniques to create fast, SEO-friendly themes, including optimizing images, implementing caching, utilizing responsive design, and adhering to SEO principles.</p>\r\n<p>The Bubble Sort algorithm gets its name from the way smaller elements \"bubble\" to the top of the list during each pass. The algorithm works by making multiple passes through the list until the entire list is sorted. During each pass, adjacent elements are compared, and if they are out of order, they are swapped. This process continues until the largest element \"bubbles\" to the end of the list.</p>\r\n<p><iframe title=\"Sycho Psd to HTML Doctor Section | Class #6 : Salim Rana | 2021\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ivndLnky7Bo?list=PLLEaOX05IZa5q00MT47e3ELbmve-3KM5h\"></iframe></p>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Active', '2023-03-07 03:54:53', '2023-06-13 08:43:05'),
(6, 1, 'WordPress Plugin APIs', 'wordpress-plugin-apis', '\"\"', '{\"topics\":[\"11\"],\"course_id\":\"1\"}', '<p>This lesson focuses on leveraging WordPress Plugin APIs to extend functionality. Learners will explore APIs such as the Options API, Metadata API, Shortcode API, and AJAX API to enhance their plugin development skills.</p>', '<p>This lesson focuses on leveraging WordPress Plugin APIs to extend functionality. Learners will explore APIs such as the Options API, Metadata API, Shortcode API, and AJAX API to enhance their plugin development skills.</p>\r\n<p><iframe class=\"bd-class-lesson-video\" title=\"Sycho Psd to HTML | Class #1 : Salim Rana | 2021\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/WY44eFBjZQs?list=PLLEaOX05IZa5q00MT47e3ELbmve-3KM5h\"></iframe></p>', '', '', '', NULL, 'Active', '2023-06-13 08:49:15', '2023-06-13 08:49:15'),
